{"quote": "Prudens quaestio dimidium scientiae", "page_title": "Roger Bacon", "page_bio": "Roger Bacon (c. 1214 \u2013 1294), also known as Doctor Mirabilis (Latin: \"wonderful teacher\"), was an English theologian, philosopher and Franciscan friar. An English philosopher who placed considerable emphasis on empiricism, he was one of the earliest European advocates of the modern scientific method. Later studies have emphasized his reliance on occult and alchemical traditions. All his theoretical writings were originally in Latin.", "page_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roger Bacon"}